        24 September 2021 - 30 September 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (24/09/2021 – 30/09/2021):

        🔴 (Negative)

        1) ‘Drive’ looks to be stalling out here! It’s so typical how everyone starts getting tired of this in the same week that it grows on me massively, isn’t it?

        2) What the is this ‘Bad Day’ rubbish? His “singing” (if we can even call it that?) reminds of Blackbear but a million times more annoying & the lyrics are somehow even more ill-wishing than ‘I Hope’ (which was my second least favourite song of last year). That was my first listen of it & it’ll almost certainly be the last! I’ll stick with the Daniel Powter song of the same name, thank you very much.

        3) ‘Need To Know’, ‘Excuses’, ‘Pain’ & ‘Talk About’ all got hit by ACR this week! I know a few people are going to be very happy about the latter though (it soured on me a bit anyway, but I still don’t mind it).

        4) ‘Psycho’ continues to go insanely underappreciated! No, I won’t stop banging on about it just yet either, it’s honestly one of my favourite songs of the decade so far now.

        5) Drake beat Lil Nas X on the albums chart by just under 500 combined sales (more on the latter in a bit though).

        🟠 (Mixed)

        1) ‘Shivers’ gets its second week at #1, meaning Ed has ruled there for the past 13 weeks now! Honestly, I have no strong opinion on this either way anymore. The song itself is fine enough; upbeat if generic production, Ed sounds a bit more raw than usual here despite the continued “cracks” when he hits his upper range, while the lyrics are more cheesy than cringeworthy! Here’s my concern though, we’ve seen Ed use this same formula for literally years now. From a commercial viewpoint, I totally get why he’s doing this (look at how well ‘Bad Habits’ & ‘Shape Of You’ did), but from an artistic perspective, I feel that his past few singles have been played incredibly safe & tried way too hard to maintain his mainstream presence! Like, he’s had 11 #1 hits in the UK now, so you’d think he’d at least be a bit more experimental with his genres going into the release of ‘=’ in a few weeks’ time & my worry is that if he doesn’t attempt stepping back out of his comfort zone soon (which we all know he’s more than capable of doing & usually incredibly well), then I’m getting the feeling that this’ll be his worst album to date, even some of the die-hard fans will probably agree with that.

        2) ‘Obsessed With You’ held up far better than I expected it to! Okay, it’s not precisely bad coming from Central Cee, but why are we letting this stick around & allowing the song it samples (‘Just For Me’ by Pinkpantheress, a much better song in my opinion) tank? :(

        3) ‘Love Nwantiti [Ah Ah Ah]’ is really gathering momentum & even ended up breaking the Top 10 this week! It’s far from my favourite Afrobeats song, but between this & ‘Essence’, it’s nice to see this culture making another resurgence.

        4) ‘24/5’ dropped off a fair bit from last week, but Radio 1 still love it, so that gives me hope that it’ll stabilise & make a comeback soon!

        🟢 (Positive)

        1) ‘Cold Heart [PNAU Remix]’ surpasses almost everyone’s expectations to take the runner-up position! One artist here is a music icon & the other is one of my favourite popstars of the past few years. A really addictive disco bop for both the older & younger generations, which isn’t something you get to say a lot in 2021! I absolutely love the interpolation of ‘Rocket Man’ on this too.

        2) Lil Nas X might’ve narrowly missed out on the #1 album tonight, but the good news over here is that ‘Industry Baby’ & ‘That’s What I Want’ are the most popular tracks on it, with the former of these now in the Top 3, since they were both among my personal favourites from ‘Montero’ too (although ‘Lost In The Citadel’ being here really would’ve been the icing on the cake). Between this & aforementioned boost for ‘Love Nwantiti’, this week was a massively successful one for black singers in the charts! ✊🏿

        3) Wait! ‘Take My Breath’ actually went back up for once? Maybe the British public finally listened to my pleads to make this a hit after all, haha.

        4) ‘Better Days’ climbed up a few places again this week! I would it would’ve been here a lot sooner, but hey, better late than never, I guess.

        💚 (Really Positive)

        1) ‘Wildest Dreams [Taylor’s Version]’ outpeaks the original 2014 re-recording by 15 places! I guess the main difference this time is that Taylor’s tone is a bit deeper in parts, so her vocals become slightly less raspy & smooth because of that. You can definitely tell that her voice has matured immensely since then, but I don’t know, I feel like the original has just a bit more of a magical feel to it & is more reminiscent of “classic Taylor”, while I didn’t really find that with most of the re-released ‘Fearless’ tracks from earlier this year! Ah, I don’t really care though, this is still an absolutely incredible remake of a song that I absolutely adored even before she announced this. I’m so happy that she’s rightfully getting ownership of her older albums back & I can’t wait to see what she has in store for us when she gives ‘Red’ a new lease of life in November! 😍

        My latest personal chart (replace the * with an “o”): www.crownnote.c*m/charts/piran/pirans-top-50-8
